# DOMMx YAML Translator  
EN → Multi-language Corporate Translator  
(OpenAI Batch + Persistent Cache)

---

## 🎯 Purpose

Utility to translate DOMMx YAML domain files from US English into structured corporate target languages while:

- Preserving YAML layout and structure
- Preserving quotes and formatting
- Preserving acronyms and governance terminology
- Skipping technical keys like `cross_reference`
- Maintaining same filename output
- Using persistent translation cache
- Supporting multi-language output folders
- Supporting CLI-based language selection

Designed for controlled enterprise-grade content localization.

---

# 🏗 Architecture

BASE_DIR  
│  
├── data/  
│   └── domains/  
│       └── us/               ← INPUT YAMLs (source language)  
│  
├── utils/  
│   └── yaml-translator/  
│       ├── translator.py     ← This script  
│       ├── _cache/  
│       │   └── translation_<lang>_cache.json  
│       └── output/  
│           └── <lang>/  
│               └── *.yaml    ← Translated output  

---

# 📁 Paths & Resolution

## Base

BASE_DIR = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent.parent  
DOMAINS_DIR = BASE_DIR / "data" / "domains"

## Input

data/domains/us/*.yaml  

Controlled by:

INPUT_FOLDER = DOMAINS_DIR / "us"

## Output (Dynamic)

utils/yaml-translator/output/<language>/*.yaml  

The output folder is dynamically created at runtime based on the CLI parameter.

## Cache (Dynamic)

utils/yaml-translator/_cache/translation_<language>_cache.json  

Each language has its own isolated persistent cache file.

